fields.label: Hook
fields.message:
Run via a wordpress filter.

apply_filter('genimage_get_instance', $filter_slug, $source_objects, $saves_array, $dimensions);

Description

You can run an instance of the generative image plugin via the 'genimage_get_instance' filter.

Parameters

(string) $filter_slug

slug name of the filter to run. i.e. 'test_filter'


(array) $source_objects

An array of WP_Term / WP_Post source objects. i.e. [ 0 => WP_Post, 1 => WP_Post, 2 => WP_Post ]


(array) $saves_array

Which conversions to run. i.e. [ 'svg' => true, 'png' => false, 'jpg' => true ]


(array) $dimensions

Optional variable that will change the size of the output SVG. Width, Height in pixels. i.e. [ 0 => '640', 1 => '480' ]


Returned

Returns true on success.
